libdftw
------------------------------------------
A distributed and decentralized filesystem treewalk function, similiar to the
interface of linux's ftw(3). libdftw automatically and dynamically balances
the treewalk workload across many nodes in a large distributed system.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1
  libcircle2-0.2.1-rc.1-1bl1
  libdftw-devel-0.0.2-1bl1
  libdftw0-0.0.2-1bl1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.0.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/hpc/libdftw

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/hpc/libdftw/archive/v0.0.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libdftw-0.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libdftw-0.0.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libdftw-0.0.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdftw-0.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdftw0-0.0.2-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libdftw-devel-0.0.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libdftw)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libdftw.README
  /usr/share/doc/libdftw/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libdftw/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libdftw/HACKING.md

(libdftw0)
  /usr/bin/cygdftw-0.dll

(libdftw-devel)
  /usr/include/libdftw.h
  /usr/lib/libdftw.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libdftw.pc

------------------

